constructor.details: The ASSET_TYPE, necessary for the deposit and withdraw logic in the Accounts, is "2" for Uniswap V3 Liquidity Positions (ERC721).

params.nonFungiblePositionManager: The contract address of the protocols NonFungiblePositionManager.
params.registry_: The contract address of the Registry.

params.asset: The contract address of the asset.
params.creditor: The contract address of the Creditor.

returns.collateralFactor: The collateral factor of the asset for the Creditor, 4 decimals precision.
returns.liquidationFactor: The liquidation factor of the asset for the Creditor, 4 decimals precision.

params.asset: The contract address of the asset.
params.creditor: The contract address of the Creditor.

returns.collateralFactor: The collateral factor of the asset for a given Creditor, with 4 decimals precision.
returns.liquidationFactor: The liquidation factor of the asset for a given Creditor, with 4 decimals precision.
returns.valueInUsd: The value of the asset denominated in USD, with 18 Decimals precision.

params.asset: The contract address of the asset.

returns._0: A boolean, indicating if the asset is allowed.

processDirectDeposit(address,address,uin.details: super.processDirectDeposit checks that msg.sender is the Registry.

params.asset: The contract address of the asset.
params.creditor: The contract address of the Creditor.

returns.recursiveCalls: The number of calls done to different asset modules to process the deposit/withdrawal of the asset.

processDirectWithdrawal(address,address,.details: super.processDirectWithdrawal checks that msg.sender is the Registry.If the asset is withdrawn, remove its liquidity from the mapping. If we would keep the liquidity of the asset in storage, _getUnderlyingAssets() would keep using the liquidity of the asset at the time of deposit. This might result in a wrongly calculated getValue() of the non-deposited asset (for off-chain purposes).

params.asset: The contract address of the asset.
params.creditor: The contract address of the Creditor.

processIndirectDeposit(address,address,u.details: super.processIndirectDeposit checks that msg.sender is the Registry.deltaExposureUpperAssetToAsset of a Uniswap V3 LP must be either 0 or 1 for processIndirectDeposit().

params.asset: The contract address of the asset.
params.creditor: The contract address of the Creditor.
params.deltaExposureUpperAssetToAsset: The increase or decrease in exposure of the upper asset to the asset of this Asset Module since last interaction.
params.exposureUpperAssetToAsset: The amount of exposure of the upper asset to the asset of this Asset Module.

returns.recursiveCalls: The number of calls done to different asset modules to process the deposit/withdrawal of the asset.
returns.usdExposureUpperAssetToAsset: The USD value of the exposure of the upper asset to the asset of this Asset Module, 18 decimals precision.

processIndirectWithdrawal(address,addres.details: super.processIndirectWithdrawal checks that msg.sender is the Registry.If the asset is withdrawn, remove its liquidity from the mapping. If we would keep the liquidity of the asset in storage, _getUnderlyingAssets() would keep using the liquidity of the asset at the time of deposit. This might result in a wrongly calculated getValue() of the non-deposited asset (for off-chain purposes).deltaExposureUpperAssetToAsset of a Uniswap V3 LP must be either 0 or -1 for processIndirectWithdrawal(). But we do NOT revert if the value is different from 0 or -1, since this would block withdrawals and hence liquidations, which is worse as having wrongly calculated exposures.

params.asset: The contract address of the asset.
params.creditor: The contract address of the creditor.
params.deltaExposureUpperAssetToAsset: The increase or decrease in exposure of the upper asset to the asset of this Asset Module since last interaction.
params.exposureUpperAssetToAsset: The amount of exposure of the upper asset to the asset of this Asset Module.

returns.usdExposureUpperAssetToAsset: The USD value of the exposure of the upper asset to the asset of this Asset Module, 18 decimals precision.

setProtocol().details: Since all assets will have the same contract address, only the NonfungiblePositionManager has to be added to the Registry.

params.creditor: The contract address of the Creditor.
params.maxUsdExposureProtocol_: The maximum USD exposure of the protocol for each Creditor, denominated in USD with 18 decimals precision.
params.riskFactor: The risk factor of the asset for the Creditor, 4 decimals precision.

isAllowed(address,uint256).notice: Checks for a token address and the corresponding id if it is allowed.

processDirectDeposit(address,address,uin.notice: Increases the exposure to an asset on a direct deposit.

processDirectWithdrawal(address,address,.notice: Decreases the exposure to an asset on a direct withdrawal.

processIndirectDeposit(address,address,u.notice: Increases the exposure to an asset on an indirect deposit.

processIndirectWithdrawal(address,addres.notice: Decreases the exposure to an asset on an indirect withdrawal.

setProtocol().notice: Adds the mapping from the NonfungiblePositionManager to this Asset Module in this Registry.

setRiskParameters(address,uint112,uint16.notice: Sets the risk parameters of the Protocol for a given Creditor.
